(tested on ubuntu 18.04 LTS, with ROS Melodic and CoppeliaSim_Edu_V4_0_0_Ubuntu18_04)

1.  open the roscore and vrep simulation
    $cd ../Projects
    $chmod a+x start.sh
    $./start.sh


3. Open a new terminal (or tab) and run:
   $ cd {path_to_framework}/Slalom/projects/catkin_ws/
   $ catkin_make

4. Open a new terminal (or tab) and run:
   $ cd {path_to_framework}/Slalom/projects/catkin_ws/
   $ source ./devel/setup.bash
   $ rosrun keyboard keyboard

   This node is for running kryboard control mode which can config in main_gecko_controller.cpp
   Where, manual control by keyboard (MANUAL 1) or autonomous mode (MANUAL 0)

   #define MANUAL 1

   And keyboard conmand is following:
   a = left
   d = right
   w = forward
   s = backward 
            
 
